/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542219348\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"c3f9afc0-a63e-41f2-92e5-22183b5398be\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219348/LamaConductor_Anisotropy.0005.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330547139&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=434&amp;height=434 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219348/LamaConductor_Anisotropy.0005.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330547139&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=217&amp;height=217 1x\"></span><p style=\"text-align: center;\">0.8</p></td><td class=\"confluenceTd\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"LamaConductor_Anisotropy.0006.jpg\" width=\"217\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219348/LamaConductor_Anisotropy.0006.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330547139&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=217&amp;height=217\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542219348/LamaConductor_Anisotropy.0006.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330547139&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"800\" data-width=\"800\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542219360\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"LamaConductor_Anisotropy.0006.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542219348\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"105f512e-db9d-4512-902d-d304232527ca\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219348/LamaConductor_Anisotropy.0006.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330547139&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=434&amp;height=434 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219348/LamaConductor_Anisotropy.0006.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330547139&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=217&amp;height=217 1x\"></span><p style=\"text-align: center;\">1.0</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Rotation : 0<br/><br/></p><p><strong>Direction</strong></p><p>Overrides the built-in surface direction using a signal from a pattern, which may be referred to as &quot;brushing direction&quot; for brushed or textured metals.</p><p><strong>Rotation</strong></p><p>Rotates the direction (possibly defined above) 0 to 360 degrees around the surface normal.</p><div class=\"embeddedObject conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"8d4f54e9-8289-4334-b7b1-807e178d2695\" data-macro-id=\"c7ca2935-9e8e-45ab-950e-1fe0b7b34136\" data-macro-name=\"multimedia\">\n    <video src=\"/wiki/download/attachments/542219348/RenderMan_AninRotation.mp4\" height=\"380\" width=\"960\" controls=\"\">\n        Your browser does not support the HTML5 video element\n</video>\n\n</div><p><br/>Rotation Example : 0 - 1<br/><br/></p><hr/><h3 id=\"LamaConductor-AdvancedParameters\">Advanced Parameters</h3><p><strong>Exterior IOR</strong></p><p>This defines the exterior medium IOR be it air (the default), water, or a layered material like a varnish on top using a Stack node.</p><p><strong>Energy Compensation</strong></p><p>This allows you to add energy to the result as microfacet or very rough materials may lose energy and artificially darken the result.</p><p><strong>Surface Mollification</strong></p><p>This defines the roughness based on curvature and may help reduce fireflies or bright pixels/artifacts in rendering.</p><p><strong>Motion Mollification</strong></p><p>This defines the roughness based on the motion of the object and may help reduce fireflies or bright pixels/artifacts in rendering.</p><p><strong>Lobe Name</strong></p><p>Defines the Arbitrary Output Variable (AOV) name for the resulting Light Path Expression (LPE)</p><p><strong>Matte</strong></p><p>This defines the name of the lobe output of the final lobe weight to an Arbitrary Output Variable (AOV)</p><p><br/></p><hr/><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" width=\"64\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219348/RenderManFundamentals_logo.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330550014&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=64&amp;height=64\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542219348/RenderManFundamentals_logo.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330550014&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"64\" data-width=\"64\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542219498\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderManFundamentals_logo.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542219348\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"c49ad362-637e-4e1e-97dd-e480b3ebbc34\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219348/RenderManFundamentals_logo.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330550014&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=64&amp;height=64 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542219348/RenderManFundamentals_logo.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330550014&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=64&amp;height=64 1x\"></span><p><strong>RenderMan Fundamentals</strong><br/><br/></p><iframe align=\"middle\" allowfullscreen=\"\" class=\"conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\